line_1: It tells, where other Folks mistook:
line_2: So, for the Honor of your Book,

line_1: They wonder Men should have mistook
line_2: The Tenets of their Master's Book;

line_1: And his horizon for the earth's mistook.
line_2: Resembled Robin, who around would look,
For tho it's in the Book,
When it told us, our Swords should to Plow-shares be broke:

line_1: My love, nor fear the language be mistook.
line_2: I will compose to soft and downcast look,
